title: Grain mostly higher, livestock mixed
text: CHICAGO -- Grain futures were mostly higher Monday in early trading on the Chicago Board of Trade. Wheat for December delivery was 15.50 cents higher at $5.0600 a bushel; December corn was 3.50 cents higher at $3.8340 a bushel; December oats were .50 cent higher at $2.2840 a bushel; while November soybeans were 8 cents lower at 8.8740 a bushel. Beef lower and pork mixed on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. December live cattle was 1.88 cents lower at $1.4153 a pound; November feeder cattle was 2.33 cents lower at $1.9093 a pound; December lean hogs gained .33 cent to $.6393 a pound. Share this page
